context: <b6_0>The Republic of the Congo<b6_0/> (French: <a0_0><b5_0><b8_0>République du Congo<b8_0/><b5_0/><a0_0/>), also known as Congo, Congo Republic, West Congo[citation needed], or <b9_0>Congo-Brazzaville<b9_0/>, is a country located in <a4_0>Central Africa<a4_0/>. It is bordered by five countries: <a2_0>Gabon<a2_0/> to the west; <a3_0>Cameroon<a3_0/> to the northwest; <b7_0>the <a1_0>Central African Republic<b7_0/><a1_0/> to the northeast; the Democratic Republic of the Congo to the east and south; and the Angolan exclave of Cabinda to the southwest.
